# API Design Standards

## URL Conventions

```
GET    /api/v1/<resource>            â†’ list (paginated)
GET    /api/v1/<resource>/:id        â†’ single item
POST   /api/v1/<resource>            â†’ create
PUT    /api/v1/<resource>/:id        â†’ full update
PATCH  /api/v1/<resource>/:id        â†’ partial update
DELETE /api/v1/<resource>/:id        â†’ delete
POST   /api/v1/<resource>/:id/<action> â†’ domain action (e.g. /analyze)
```

- Always prefix with `/api/v1/`
- Resources in **kebab-case plural** (`tender-items`, not `tenderItem`)
- Actions as nouns or verbs at the end of the path

## Response Shapes

```typescript
// âś… List response
{ data: T[], total: number, page: number, pageSize: number }

// âś… Single item
{ data: T }

// âś… Error (never expose stack traces in production)
{ error: string, code: string, statusCode: number }

// âś… Created
reply.status(201).send({ data: newResource })
```

## Fastify Route Plugin

```typescript
// âś… CORRECT pattern
import type { FastifyPluginAsync } from 'fastify';

const myRoutes: FastifyPluginAsync = async (fastify) => {
  fastify.get('/api/v1/resources', async (request, reply) => {
    const items = await fastify.db.resource.findMany({ ... });
    return { data: items, total: items.length };
  });
};

export default myRoutes;
```

## Query Parameters

- Pagination: `?page=1&pageSize=20` (default pageSize: 20, max: 100)
- Filtering: `?status=active&dt=2024-01-01`
- Sorting: `?sortBy=createdAt&order=desc`
- Always validate with Fastify JSON Schema on `querystring`

## OpenAPI

- Every route must have a corresponding entry in `src/openapi.ts`
- Include `summary`, `tags`, `parameters`, `requestBody`, and `responses` (200, 400, 401, 500)
- Tag groupings: `auth`, `tenders`, `providers`, `analytics`, `ai`, `documents`

## Error Handling

```typescript
// âś… Use Fastify's built-in error throwing
throw fastify.httpErrors.notFound('Tender not found');
throw fastify.httpErrors.badRequest('Invalid date format');
throw fastify.httpErrors.unauthorized('Token expired');

// âś… Wrap external calls
try {
  const result = await externalService.call();
  return { data: result };
} catch (err) {
  request.log.error({ err }, 'External service failed');
  throw fastify.httpErrors.serviceUnavailable('Service temporarily unavailable');
}
```

## Do / Don't

- âś… Keep route handlers thin â€” delegate logic to service classes
- âś… Use `query_params` pattern for parameterized queries
- âś… Log with `request.log` (structured JSON), not `console.log`
- âťŚ Never return raw Prisma errors to the client
- âťŚ Never skip input validation schemas
- âťŚ Never hardcode IDs, URLs, or secrets in route files
